{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17537808","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17537808"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:20:55+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:20:55+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16066"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16066","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16066"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.18,0.03,0.72,0.01,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8757"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63761"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8757","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8757"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question","status":"accepted","createdAt":"2024-11-22T13:06:06+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-22T13:11:27+10:30","updatedAction":"commented","acceptedAt":"2024-11-22T13:11:27+10:30","editorNotifiedAt":null,"feedbackAt":"2025-09-18 10:47:56"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16066"}},"updatedBy":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"13481"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"13481"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49200"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"2451"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4398"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4980"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"},{"type":"tags","id":"12799"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20931"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43602"}]},"lastContribution":{"data":null},"lastRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49200"}},"lastActivity":{"data":null},"lastFeedback":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63761","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/63761"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 32-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department at 34 weeks gestation with three days of worsening shortness of breath. She tested positive for COVID-19 five days ago. She has no significant medical history and takes only pregnancy vitamins. She is unvaccinated against COVID-19.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears mildly distressed. Her pulse rate is 110/min, blood pressure 125/80 mmHg, respiratory rate 24/min, SpO2 92% on room air, and temperature 37.8\u00b0C. Chest auscultation reveals bilateral crackles. The fetus is active with a fundal height appropriate for dates.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"What counselling should this patient receive about COVID and pregnancy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Pregnancy significantly increases mortality risk","Vertical transmission occurs in most cases","Management principles are similar to non-pregnant patients","Caesarean section is routinely indicated","Vaccination is contraindicated"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ECurrent evidence indicates that pregnant women with COVID-19 do not have significantly worse outcomes compared to non-pregnant women of similar age. \u003Cstrong\u003EManagement principles are similar to non-pregnant patients\u003C/strong\u003E, with the addition of fetal monitoring when appropriate.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPregnancy significantly increases mortality risk\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. While pregnant women were initially thought to be at higher risk, current data suggests that pregnancy itself does not significantly increase the risk of severe COVID-19 outcomes when compared to non-pregnant women of similar age.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVertical transmission\u003C/strong\u003E of COVID-19 from mother to fetus is possible but rare, occurring in less than 5% of cases. When it does occur, most neonates have mild or asymptomatic infection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECaesarean section\u003C/strong\u003E is not routinely indicated for COVID-19 positive mothers. The mode of delivery should be determined by standard obstetric indications. COVID-19 infection alone is not an indication for operative delivery.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVaccination\u003C/strong\u003E is strongly recommended during pregnancy. Multiple studies have demonstrated the safety and efficacy of COVID-19 vaccination in pregnancy, with benefits including passive antibody transfer to the fetus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe key principles of managing COVID-19 in pregnancy include maintaining adequate oxygenation (SpO2 \u0026gt;94%), providing appropriate supportive care, monitoring for complications, and ensuring fetal wellbeing through continuous cardiotocography when indicated. The threshold for escalation of care should be similar to non-pregnant patients.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["COVID-19 infection does not inherently have a worse prognosis in pregnant compared to non-pregnant women of similar age.","Continuous cardiotocography monitoring is required for symptomatic COVID-19 in the third trimester.","Management principles are similar between pregnant and non-pregnant patients, with additional fetal monitoring."],"references":["Royal Australian and New Zealand College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists (RANZCOG). COVID-19 guide for resource-limited environments [Internet]. East Melbourne: RANZCOG; 2020 Aug [cited 2024 Nov 22]. Available from: https://ranzcog.edu.au/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/COVID-19-Guide-for-Resource-limited-Environments-August-2020-Update.pdf"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49200"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16066"}},"ste